gomodel:SYNGO_1769  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: The extracellular domains of neuronal pentraxin receptor (NPR-ECD) and the secreted neuronal pentraxins NP1 and NARP (NP2) directly bind to GluA1-NTD\nFig.3: NPR, NP1, and NARP binding enhances GluA1 function.\n\n1/11/2017 Pim\n- The action of NP2 is not shown in synaptic setting but in HEK cells. The function of NP2 is inferred to also take place on synaptic AMPARs.. Experimental description: Mouse hippocampal neurons were prepared.\n\n23/6/2017 Pim\n-All overexpression constructs are of human species: \"The constructs encoding cDNAs of hNPR (HsCD00083063), hNP1 (HsCD00296108), and hNARP (HsCD00040444) were obtained from PlasmID (http://plasmid.med.harvard.edu/PLASMID/).\"\n- Species of GluA1-NTD overexpressed protein is not mentioned." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1769" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

